<P>
NATIONAL VIDEO RENTALS ; 'SLEEPLESS' A HOLIDAY SWEETHEART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DENNIS HUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 All the returns won't be in until next week, but some retailers are reporting 
that "Sleepless in Seattle" did anything but sleepy business during Valentine's 
Day weekend. The romantic comedy remains locked in second place, middleman in 
that same old 1-2-3 configuration seen for weeks: With "The Firm" on top and 
"Dave" in third.The oddball "Kalifornia," featuring Brad Pitt and Juliette 
Lewis, did poorly at the box office but its positive reviews are helping it 
attract a sizable rental audience. It jumped from No. 36 to No. 16--impressive 
for a film that hardly anybody saw in theaters. "Last Action Hero," the Arnold 
Schwarzenegger box-office bomb, had a strong second week, leaping from No. 13 
to No. 5. There's enough curiosity about it to lure renters during its first 
few weeks in release, but some retailers fear that bad word of mouth will 
ultimately sink it. 03,34,06,08 Rank Weeks Last on the Week Chart 1. "The Firm" 
1 7 2. "Sleepless in Seattle" 2 8 3. "Dave" 3 7 4. "Hard Target" 11 2 5. "Last 
Action Hero" 13 2 6. "Rising Sun" 4 10 7. "True Romance" 5 5 8. "Robin Hood: 
Men in Tights" 6 4 9. "Hocus Pocus" 8 5 10. "Rookie of the Year" 16 2 * 
"Coneheads" 16 2 * "Coneheads," featuring Dan Aykroyd and Jane Curtin 
re-creating their old "Saturday Night Live" characters, is doing fairly healthy 
business, jumping from No. 18 to No. 11 in its second week on the chart. Still, 
it's not doing quite as well as some retailers expected. This comedy didn't 
meet expectations during its theatrical run either. But don't count "Coneheads" 
out just yet. Its rental-market performance could pick up in the next few 
weeks. 
</P>
