<HEADLINE>
<P>
'ANGIE' BENEFIT TO OPEN WOMEN'S FILM FESTIVAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The ninth International Women's Film Festival, sponsored by Women in Film, 
will open Feb. 28 at the Avco Cinema in Westwood with a benefit screening of 
Martha Coolidge's "Angie," starring Geena Davis, Aida Turturro and Stephen Rea. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival will be held March 3-6 at Universal Studios and feature world 
premieres of Susan Shapiro's "A Fare to Remember," Julie Cypher's "Teresa's 
Tattoo" and conclude with a special screening of "Crazy in Love," a TNT 
production also directed by Coolidge. 
</P>
<P>
 Among the other offerings will be "The Last Supper," which marks Daryl 
Hannah's directorial debut, and Diane Kurys' "Love After Love." 
</P>
<P>
 There will be question-and-answers sessions with the filmmakers and various 
seminars. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 463-6040. 
</P>
