<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LONG BEACH; 3 TO BE 
ARRAIGNED TODAY IN BANK ROBBERY, SIEGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three suspected robbers who held a Long Beach bank under siege for nine hours 
Wednesday while four female bank employees hid inside face arraignment today on 
felony robbery charges, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Marcus Young, 18, of Los Angeles and two teen-agers were found hiding in 
air-conditioning ducts or on a ventilation shaft about 9 p.m. Wednesday, 
Officer Margarita DeWitt said.The four hostages had locked themselves safely in 
the vault during the incident and were rescued by a Long Beach SWAT team using 
flash-bang grenades to storm the bank at 5:45 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Police believe that Young and the two youths, who are 16 and 17, vaulted bank 
tellers' counters about noon Wednesday, beginning a standoff that lasted until 
after 9 p.m. and virtually shut down the bustling business district at Pacific 
Coast Highway and Ximeno Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Young is being held in lieu of $50,000 bail and the teen-agers, whose names 
were not released because of their ages, are in a juvenile hall, DeWitt said. 
All three are from Los Angeles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
