<P>
ELDERLY MAN DIES AFTER DRIVING CAR INTO ONCOMING TRAFFIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An elderly man died late Wednesday when he drove his car into oncoming 
traffic, possibly after suffering a heart attack, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 The man, whose identity was not disclosed pending notification of next of kin, 
was backing his car out of a driveway on Burbank Boulevard just west of 
Sepulveda Boulevard at 10:40 p.m. and continued through two lanes of traffic, 
across a center divider and into another lane of oncoming traffic, said 
Detective Don Bellante of the Los Angeles Police Department's Valley Traffic 
Division. 
</P>
<P>
 "He could have had a heart attack," Bellante said. "It has all the indications 
of that because of the driving and because of the impact." 
</P>
<P>
 The man's car was struck by another vehicle, but suffered only minor damage. 
He was pronounced dead on arrival at Sherman Oaks Hospital and Health Center, 
Bellante said. 
</P>
<P>
 An autopsy is being performed to determine the cause of death, Bellante said. 
</P>
