WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; HEARING TO ADDRESS DIETARY SUPPLEMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Experts from the medical community, vitamin users and officials from the Food 
and Drug Administration will meet in Ventura today to debate the wisdom of 
regulating dietary supplements. 
</P>
<P>
 During the next few months, strict new FDA regulations are scheduled to take 
effect to control over-the-counter sale of certain supplements and vitamins. 
</P>
<P>
 Rep. Elton Gallegly (R-Simi Valley) who is leading a congressional effort to 
overturn the new regulations, has organized today's public hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 "We think the consumers should have access to these supplements," said John 
Frith, Gallegly's press secretary. "But there will be people from both sides of 
the issue at the hearing." 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to medical and government experts, celebrities including Morgan 
Fairchild, Heather Thomas, Eddie Albert and Los Angeles Raiders lineman Anthony 
Smith are scheduled to attend. 
</P>
<P>
 The meeting will be held at the Ventura Holiday Inn, 450 E. Harbor Blvd., from 
1 to 5 p.m. For more information, call 485-2300. MATTHEW MOSK 
