<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: ROD TURNER, CHIEF OF KNOWLEDGE ADVENTURE, QUITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rod Turner, president and chief executive of La Crescenta-based multimedia 
software firm Knowledge Adventure, has left the company. The firm's chairman 
and founder, Bill Gross, will assume Turner's duties on an interim basis. 
</P>
<P>
 Turner, an experienced manager of high-growth companies whom Gross himself 
helped recruit last year, said he and Gross had fundamental disagreements about 
how to guide the fledgling educational software firm. "Basically, we weren't 
able to agree on the way forward," Turner said. 
</P>
<P>
 But both sides said the conflict was mainly one of style. Gross, who has a 
reputation as a creative genius, is said to have clashed with Turner's more 
traditional management style. Knowledge Adventure, whose investors include 
Paramount Communications Inc. and AT&T, is regarded as one of the most 
promising start-ups in the fast-growing multimedia industry.  
</P>
<P>
 * Actor Billy Crystal's Face Productions named Lynne Boyarsky vice president 
of production. She previously was vice president of development at Wildwood 
Enterprises. 
</P>
<P>
 * Jess Wittenberg was named senior vice president of business and legal 
affairs with Castle Rock Entertainment, a unit of Turner Broadcasting System. 
</P>
<P>
 * QVC Network Inc. said it's changing its name to QVC Inc. and announced a 
corporate reorganization, including the retirement of President and co-founder 
Michael Boyd. Boyd will continue to consult for the home shopping channel, 
which also announced that Douglas Briggs has been promoted to the new position 
of QVC Electronic Retailing. 
</P>
