<HEADLINE>
<P>
BARGAINS / GERI COOK: BUDGET BUYS FOR BATH AND KITCHEN; * AMERICAN PREMIUM 
DISTRIBUTORS NOW OFFERS MAJOR APPLIANCES, PLUMBING ITEMS AND FIXTURES FOR 
LITTLE OVER COST. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GERI COOK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thirteen years ago, when I first discovered American Premium Distributors, 
they were selling jewelry, pens, small appliances along with a few major, plus 
some other merchandise, all at excellent prices. Since then, they purchased the 
building they occupy and expanded their operation at the same location. It's a 
whole new ballgame. 
</P>
<P>
 They liquidated the jewelry, pens and small appliances, and now deal in major 
appliances, doors, windows, plumbing and, in general, fixtures for the kitchen 
or bath at prices that hover a small percentage over cost. 
</P>
<P>
 When I revisited APD a few days after the Jan. 17 earthquake, every available 
staff member was working with a customer, poring over plans.  
</P>
<P>
 According to part-owner Stacey Fisch, daughter of founders Bob and Kevy 
Greenwald, half of the business at American Premium Distributors is from the 
sale of plumbing equipment. There are catalogues and floor models to look at 
from such companies as Kohler, Raphael, Grohe and Price-Pfister, and items are 
available at competitive prices. A single-lever kitchen faucet with pullout 
spray from Price-Pfister is popular, selling for $147 instead of the $227 list 
price. 
</P>
<P>
 A cast-iron steeping, or deeper, bathtub by Kohler is a new, sought-after 
product that lists for about $1,342. But the price here is $872. 
</P>
<P>
 Whatever the specific need, Fisch recommends that the homeowner purchase 
plumbing fixtures directly to eliminate any markup by trades people. 
</P>
<P>
 Major appliances represent another large part of this family-owned and 
-operated business. Almost all of the upscale names in built-in or 
free-standing appliances are available.  
</P>
<P>
 Nutone, Kitchen-Aid, Caloric, Vent-A-Hood, Gaggenau and Jenn-Air are a few. 
One Jenn-Air built-in single, self-cleaning convection oven sells elsewhere for 
about $750, but the price here is $649. A popular Whirlpool side-by-side, 
25-cubic-foot refrigerator with ice and water through the door is $1,159 
instead of the $1,400 many retailers ask. 
</P>
<P>
 Door and window manufacturing companies represented by APD include A.A.W. 
Inc., International, Anderson, Fleetwood and Velux. One standard size interior 
paneled door from T. M. Cobb is $34.50 instead of $69.60. Where and When What: 
American Premium Distributors. 
</P>
<P>
 Location: 8644 W. Washington Blvd., Culver City. 
</P>
<P>
 Hours: 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Tuesdays through Fridays, 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. 
Saturdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Cards: None. 
</P>
<P>
 Call: (310) 839-2338. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA021894-0151 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 014679 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
February 18, 1994, Friday, Valley Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Valley Life; Page 31 
</P>
