<HEADLINE>
<P>
STALKING THE NOT-SO-WILD ORCHID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN HEEGER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For veteran or budding orchid enthusiasts, the San Fernando Valley Orchid 
Society meets at 7:30 p.m. the first Thursday of every month at the Northridge 
Woman's Club, 18401 Lassen St. Contact Donald Wong at (818) 368-0393. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Useful publications for orchid collectors, growers and admirers: 
</P>
<P>
 * American Orchid Society Bulletin, 6000 S. Olive Ave., West Palm Beach, FL 
33405.Telephone (407) 585-8666. 
</P>
<P>
 * Orchid Digest. Write Mrs. Norman H. Atkinson, P.O. Box 916, Carmichael, CA 
95609-0916. 
</P>
<P>
 These nurseries are good sources of orchids, supplies and advice: 
</P>
<P>
