<HEADLINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH STATE LOSES IN OVERTIME; BIG WEST: ANDERSON SCORES SIX OF HIS 20 
POINTS IN EXTRA PERIOD TO LEAD UTAH STATE, 80-76. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roddie Anderson scored six of his 20 points in overtime to lead Utah State to 
an 80-76 Big West Conference victory over Long Beach State Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
 The Aggies, 11-11 overall and 8-6 in the Big West, started the overtime with 
an 8-1 run to lead, 75-68, with 2:46 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah State made five of six free throws in the final 39 seconds, with Jarobi 
Kemp making four of four to finish with 14 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Nathan Wickizer had 19 points and nine rebounds and reserve Corwin Woodard 
scored 15 points to help the Aggies to their fifth consecutive victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Rod Hannibal led Long Beach (12-8, 7-6) with 29 points, 24 in the second half. 
Mike Atkinson scored 17 points and Terrance O'Kelley 15.  
</P>
<P>
 Hannibal scored eight points in a 14-0 run that gave the 49ers their first 
lead, 43-42, with 13:59 to play. 
</P>
<P>
 Utah State's Jon Wickizer sent the game into overtime with a layup with nine 
seconds to play. 
</P>
<P>
 O'Kelley missed a three-point attempt and Nathan Wickizer pulled down the 
rebound. 
</P>
