<HEADLINE>
<P>
ECHO OF YESTERDAY WINS FEATURE RACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Echo of Yesterday, ridden by Chris McCarron, won a stretch duel with favored 
Bossanova to capture the $66,100 feature race at Santa Anita on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Echo of Yesterday, the second choice in the wagering, finished a half-length 
in front of Bossanova, ridden by Eddie Delahoussaye. 
</P>
<P>
 His Legacy was third, another 1 1/4 lengths behind in the one-mile race for 
4-year-olds and up. 
</P>
<P>
 The race was scheduled for the turf, but was switched to the main track 
because of rain. 
</P>
<P>
 Echo of Yesterday, a 5-year-old gelded son of Pirate's Bounty, carried 115 
pounds and was clocked in 1:34. 
</P>
<P>
 Echo of Yesterday paid $7.20, $3.20 and $2.60. Bossanova, who carried 115, 
returned $3.20 and $2.40. His Legacy, ridden by Alex Solis and carrying 114, 
paid $2.80. 
</P>
<P>
 Eight California-bred runners contested the race. 
</P>
<P>
 Echo of Yesterday, trained by Ron Ellis, has won seven of 12 career races. 
</P>
