<HEADLINE>
<P>
GEORGIA CONFIRMS GAMSAKHURDIA DEATH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Georgian government confirmed the death of ousted President Zviad 
Gamsakhurdia, saying his body was dug up Thursday from a shallow grave in 
western Georgia for reburial in southern Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 A joint commission from Georgia and Russia's Chechnya region, and accompanying 
journalists, identified the partially decomposed body, which had a gunshot 
wound through the head. "Unfortunately, I am certain that this is the body of 
Zviad Konstantinovich Gamsakhurdia," said Guram Sharidze, a member of the 
delegation. 
</P>
<P>
 Gamsakhurdia, who had lived in exile in Chechnya since being overthrown in 
January, 1992, waged an unsuccessful campaign to return to power last fall. His 
widow, Manana, announced in January that he had committed suicide Dec. 31. 
</P>
