<HEADLINE>
<P>
JOHNSON, RILEY TO COACH FINAL CONFERENCE GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cypress' Don Johnson and Fullerton's Colleen Riley will coach their final 
regular-season games tonight. Both are retiring after the season. 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson, the state's winningest community college men's basketball coach, 
takes his Chargers to Riverside for a 7 p.m. Orange Empire Conference 
game.Cypress (15-17, 6-7) has won four in a row. Riverside (25-6, 11-2) is tied 
for first with Saddleback. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback (21-7, 11-2) goes against Irvine Valley (17-14, 5-8) at Capistrano 
Valley High at 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Riley, the state's winningest community college women's basketball coach, and 
Fullerton (19-13, 7-4) can clinch at least a tie for second with a victory over 
first-place Golden West (28-4, 10-1). The 7 p.m. game is at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The women's Southern California playoff pairings will be announced Sunday and 
the men's on Tuesday. STEVE KRESAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
