<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHERN SECTION GIRLS' SOCCER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other Division II wild-card games: 
</P>
<P>
 Estancia 3, Aliso Niguel 1 -- Tracie Manz, Dori Marsh and Jackie Connelly each 
scored for Estancia (11-6-6). The Eagles will play at El Modena, the Century 
League champion, Saturday.Nicole Trott scored the only goal for Aliso Niguel 
(8-7-3), which was competing in its first playoff game in any sport. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach Poly 2, Cypress 1 (OT) -- Rhonda Ennis scored the game-winning goal 
with six minutes remaining in overtime. She also scored the tying goal six 
minutes into the second half for Long Beach Poly (12-4-4). Carrie Powell scored 
and Kim Lumsdaine had 12 saves for Cypress, which made the playoffs for the 
first time in 14 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon 1, Fullerton 0 -- Freshman Kerry Anderson scored and freshman 
goalkeeper Robin Schmidt had six saves in her 11th shutout for Canyon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
