<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAIN FORCES POSTPONEMENT OF SEVERAL GAMES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thursday's rain forced the postponement of a number of high school and 
community college events. 
</P>
<P>
 On the high school level, the Southern Section Division II boys' soccer 
playoff game between Capistrano Valley and Santa Ana Valley was moved to 3 p.m. 
today at Santa Ana Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The Southern Section Division I wild-card girls' soccer game between Dana 
Hills and Newport Harbor was rescheduled for 3:15 p.m. today at Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
 On the community college level, Orange Coast's first-round baseball game 
against San Mateo in the Hancock tournament will be played at 2 p.m. today. The 
OCC men's tennis match at Southwestern has been rescheduled for March 1. And 
OCC's softball game against San Bernardino was postponed with no new date set. 
</P>
<P>
 The Golden West men's tennis match against San Diego Mesa will be made up at 2 
p.m. today and its track meet was rescheduled to April 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
