<HEADLINE>
<P>
RAIBON LEADS ST. MARGARET'S PAST VALLEY TORAH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Damian Raibon scored 29 points, including 19 in the first half, to lead St. 
Margaret's to a 102-32 victory over Valley Torah in a first-round Division V-AA 
playoff game Thursday at St. Margaret's High. 
</P>
<P>
 Although Raibon also had 12 rebounds and six blocked shots, Coach Rick Bauer 
was quick to point out after the game, "It wasn't a one-man show.Everyone 
contributed." 
</P>
<P>
 The Tartans (19-3) had five players score in double figures. Lupe Rodriguez 
had 14, Danny Gomez 12, David Tomlinson 11 and Bobby Baker 10. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's put away the Patriots early, outscoring them, 22-6, in the 
first quarter. Raibon, who scored 13 in the first quarter, sparked the offense 
with three slam-dunks in the opening quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 "We knew we had to put them away early and our fast break was really clicking 
tonight," Bauer said. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley Torah (9-7) was led by Steve Hami with 12 points. SCOTT JONES 
</P>
</TEXT>
