<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE WOMEN'S BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; BRADSHAW SCORES 23, TITANS RALLY TO BEAT 
NEVADA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Although Nevada led by seven at the end of the first half, Fullerton came back 
for a 70-61 Big West Conference victory in a women's basketball game Thursday 
at Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Shayla Bradshaw scored 23 points, including two three-pointers, to lead 
the Titans (3-18, 2-11).Forward Autumn Hollyfield added 17 points, including 
five three-pointers, and Shefonda Colbert had 15 points and 13 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Center Shelley Chatfield scored 18 points for Nevada (3-16, 0-13), which is 
winless in conference play. 
</P>
<P>
 In another conference game: 
</P>
<P>
 UC Santa Barbara 73, UC Irvine 65 -- The Gauchos were at the free-throw line 
all night, and made 31 of 40 free throws. 
</P>
<P>
 Tamera Thomas and Jinelle Williams each scored 14 points for UC Irvine (2-19, 
1-12). 
</P>
