<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; DISTRICT CHANCELLOR JOINS TRUSTEES PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coast Community College District Chancellor William M. Vega has been appointed 
to the advisory committee of presidents for the Assn. of Community College 
Trustees. 
</P>
<P>
 The advisory committee was established to ensure that community college 
leaders have a voice in evaluating the ACCT's educational programs. 
</P>
<P>
 ACCT is a nonprofit educational organization for members of governing boards 
at public, private, community, technical and junior colleges whose purpose is 
to strengthen people's knowledge of community colleges and how they are 
governed. 
</P>
<P>
 Vega is the fifth chancellor of the Coast Community College district. He 
previously was president of Coast Community College, one of the district's 
three schools, and currently serves on the board of directors of the American 
Assn. of Community Colleges, a national group promoting the interests of the 
country's 1,200 community colleges. 
</P>
