<TEXT>
<P>
 A 75-year-old man suffering from Alzheimer's disease was found in Lake Havasu 
on Wednesday evening, one day after leaving home on an errand. 
</P>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies said Ernest William Constable had recently moved to Lake 
Forest and became confused and disoriented while searching for a hardware store 
Tuesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
 After wandering in the Saddleback Valley area for 2 1/2 hours, Constable 
filled his car's gas tank and drove to a mobile home that he and his wife owned 
in Lake Havasu. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly after 6 p.m. on Wednesday, family members contacted friends in the 
mobile home park and found that Constable was safe. 
