<HEADLINE>
<P>
STUDENT VANISHES WITHOUT A CLUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK I. PINSKY, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police and family members are searching for a 20-year-old dean's list student 
at Cal State Fullerton who has been missing for nearly a week. 
</P>
<P>
 Cathy Torrez finished her shift at Sav-On Drugs in the 100 block of East Yorba 
Linda Boulevard at 8 p.m. Saturday, said goodby to co-workers and has not been 
seen since, police said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 "None of what we can actually confirm is good," Sgt. David M. Taylor said. 
</P>
<P>
 Torrez's purse, clothing, jewelry, makeup and belongings are all at the house 
she shared with her family, along with several un-cashed paychecks, police 
said. There has been no activity on her bank account since her disappearance, 
and Torrez's friends have not been contacted. 
</P>
<P>
 Her car, a 1990 burgundy Toyota Corolla, license plate 2RMC 785, also has not 
been seen. 
</P>
<P>
 "We don't have any sign of anything really good here," Taylor said. "We're 
into five days now. I'd be very glad to know that she's not injured or dead." 
</P>
<P>
 Torrez's mother, Mary Bennett, 45, said: "It's been very devastating for all 
of us, something I wouldn't wish on anybody. It's a nightmare in itself. 
There's no day or night. We're all in limbo. The whole family is upset, nobody 
can make heads or tails of this. I can't think straight any more. . . ." 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to her job at Sav-On, Torrez worked as a bilingual aide at two 
Placentia public schools to help pay for college. She was an honors graduate 
from Valencia High School. 
</P>
<P>
 Torrez has dark brown hair and is 4 feet, 10 inches tall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
