<P>
ORANGE COUNTY BRIEFLY: REGENCY SETS RECORD DATE FOR MERGER VOTE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Regency Health Services Inc.said Thursday that its board of directors has set 
March 3 as the record date for stockholders to vote on a merger with Care 
Enterprises. 
</P>
<P>
 Regency plans to hold a special meeting of stockholders at 9 a.m. April 4 at 
the Sheraton Hotel Newport Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 "We anticipate mailing the proxy material March 7 and (shareholders) either 
can mail in their vote or they can show up at the meeting and cast their vote 
then," according to a Regency spokeswoman. 
</P>
<P>
 Regency announced Dec. 21 that it has signed a merger agreement with Care 
Enterprises, a Tustin-based operator of 51 nursing homes and rehabilitation 
centers, of which 38 are in California. The others are in Ohio, New Mexico and 
West Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
 Regency, based in Newport Beach, operates 43 nursing homes in California. 
</P>
