<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; NORTH HOLLYWOOD GIRLS HOLD OFF SYLMAR, 76-66 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sylmar High's girls trailed North Hollywood by 24 early in the fourth quarter 
Thursday night. Then Nadra Manley took over, scoring 13 of her team-high 25 
points to bring the Spartans within seven. 
</P>
<P>
 However, North Hollywood (14-6, 10-0 in league play) held on to win, 76-66, 
and remain undefeated in Valley Pac-8 Conference play, spoiling a chance for 
the Spartans (17-2, 10-1) to do the same. 
</P>
<P>
 Senior Forward Darvena Merritt led all scorers with 31 points and hauled down 
10 rebounds for the Huskies. Teammate Anna Celaya scored 23 points and had nine 
of her team's 24 steals. Sylmar's Manley took 17 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 64, Sherman Oaks CES 26 -- Led by Allana Torres (21) and Mirna Martinez 
(13), the Vikings outrebounded the Knights, 47-12, in a Valley Pac-8 Conference 
game. 
</P>
<P>
 Ese Akpou scored a game-high 20 points for Sherman Oaks CES. BOYS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Birmingham 47, Poly 44 (OT) -- Scott James made a three-point basket with two 
seconds left in overtime for host Birmingham (8-10, 5-6) in the Mid-Valley 
League game. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 98, Canoga Park 72 -- Kenyatta Niles recorded a triple-double for the 
Vikings (9-12, 6-5), scoring 18 points and grabbing 11 rebounds while also 
posting 13 assists. Monroe had five players score in double figures, including 
Shaka Steiner who had 21. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant 55, Van Nuys 37 -- Junior Guard Ron Patterson scored 20 points to lead 
the Lancers (18-4, 9-1) in a Valley Pac-8 Conference game. BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys 4, Fairfax 1 -- Carlos Carillo and Willie Tovar each scored two goals 
to lead the Wolves (9-2-2) at home in the first round of the City Section 
playoffs. 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 2, Los Angeles 1 -- Monroe, last season's City Section runner-up, upset 
the Romans in a wild-card match with second-half goals by Wilson Lopez and Juan 
Juarez. Goalkeeper Herbert Oliva made 10 saves for the Vikings (5-2-3). GIRLS' 
SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 Louisville 5, San Marcos 4 (2 OTs) -- Arial Garcia scored with a minute left 
in the second overtime period to cap the Royals' come-from-behind victory in 
the Southern Section Division II wild-card match at San Marcos. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley 5, Santa Monica 0 -- Heather Stanley scored two goals for Simi 
Valley in the Southern Section Division I wild-card match at Santa Monica. 
</P>
